    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-12-13T05:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-12-13T05:30:00-05:00" n="568"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d568">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">745A.5/12–1352: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in India</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BCB1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowles</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New Delhi</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-12-13T16:00:00+05:30"
                            >December 13, 1952—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2433. During conversation with <persName corresp="#p_MST1">Mills</persName> and
                        <persName corresp="#p_WE1">Wilkins</persName> yesterday <gloss
                        target="#t_IN1">Ind</gloss> Foreign Sec <persName corresp="#p_NRK1">R. K.
                        Nehru</persName> stated for info of <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> that
                        <gloss target="#t_IN1">Ind</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_Amb1">Amb</gloss> in Wash had been instructed by mail Dec 3 to
                    approach <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> re extension military assistance
                    to <gloss target="#t_SoAfr1">SoAfr</gloss> by US.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_NRK1">Nehru</persName> said <gloss target="#t_GOI1"
                        >GOI</gloss> was deeply concerned to learn from <gloss target="#t_SoAfr1"
                        >SoAfr</gloss> Union Govt <hi rend="italic">Gazette</hi> of Oct 17, 1952
                    that US and SAG had concluded agmt <pb facs="1027" n="981" xml:id="pg_981"/>
                    providing for 40 million pounds sterling in procurement of milit equipment in
                    US. <persName corresp="#p_NRK1">Nehru</persName> said <gloss target="#t_GOI1"
                        >GOI</gloss> understood agreement contained two undertakings: (1) asst
                    furnished wld be used to further intl peace and security under UN Charter; (2)
                    milit equipment supplied by US “will be used solely to maintain internal
                    security”.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_NRK1">Nehru</persName> recalled <gloss target="#t_GOI1"
                        >GOI</gloss> approached <gloss target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss> 9 months ago on
                    racial question in South Africa to which <gloss target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss>
                    replied in effect that <gloss target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss> did not consider it
                    desirable to make <hi rend="italic">démarche</hi> to SAG.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d568fn1">See telegram 223, Apr. 8, <ref target="#pg_906">p.
                            906</ref>.</note> After that UN considered matter and recently passed
                    res that South Africa racial policy was likely to endanger world peace.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> was deeply concerned that milit asst to
                        <gloss target="#t_SoAfr1">SoAfr</gloss> (might be used) against groups
                    opposed to SAG’s racial policies and wld thus intensify racial conflict. In that
                    sense US-SAG agmt and UN action wld seem to be at odds with each other.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_MST1">Mills</persName> told <persName corresp="#p_NRK1"
                        >Nehru</persName> he wld inform <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> of his
                    remarks and that <gloss target="#t_IN1">Ind</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_Amb1">Amb</gloss> planned approach <gloss target="#t_Dept1"
                        >Dept</gloss> along foregoing lines.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BCB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
